# Source/Action Section Structure

When rendering a source or an action page, separate concepts clearly into independent sections when applicable:

- `Installation`: one-time setup steps to make the integration work.
- `Configuration`: choices and parameters once installed.
- `Logs / Tracking`: recent events, checks, execution status, and timestamps.
- `Notifications`: whether notifications are available and where they appear.

Only show sections that make sense for the current integration; do not force all four.

## Card Separation Rule

- One section must map to one distinct `ds-beta-control-card`.
- Do not mix multiple section concepts in a single control card.
- Keep section cards visually consistent across source/action pages.
- Keep section titles outside cards (same visual pattern as PuryFi pages).
- Preserve clear vertical rhythm between consecutive cards (visible spacing).

## Section Container and Activation Toggle Rule

- Wrap each logical section in `<section class="ds-beta-section">`.
- Every source/action page must expose an enable/disable toggle.
- Place the toggle on the same horizontal row as the page title.
- Align the toggle at the far right end of that title row (top-right of the page content area).

## Installation Drawer Rule

- When installation is completed and confirmed working, keep installation details collapsed by default in a drawer.
- If installation is missing or failing, keep installation instructions visible.
